<br>
Love is a vicious parasite, carried and spread by bards, mostly, and those of the &quot;light&quot; speaking of a happiness unparalleled, a divinity unfathomable, sighs never ending, purity, salvation, and so on.  That is their way, to sing and preach of how things should be instead of how they truly are.  For instance, how does love work?<br>
<br>
This parasite attacks both hosts, destroying their sense, their reasoning... there it thrives until something impairs it from flowing between the two.  This can happen for many reasons: one host is killed, taken away, moves on, is strong enough to expell it, or rumors create their own silent barrier between the two.  Left on it's own, it turns against it's host.<br>
<br>
This love that once made the body seem more alive attacks its host twice over to make up for what it would be taking from the other body, enfeebling it's lone host, making the host more vulnerable than ever before.  Here the cylce ends, or begins again.<br>
<br>
Either that host is destroyed as he should be, throwing himself into a pit of lava, or tries to find someone to share it with (infect with it) to ease the pain left by the gaping whole the parasite has eaten through him.<br>
<br>
As with all in life, only the strong will survive.  Only the strong can keep it from taking them to begin with. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upentapod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pentapod</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.ozemail.com.au/~pentapod/graphics/a_pod.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>WTB phat newt</span><br>  Posts: 1210<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/21/02 11:52:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.ozemail.com.au/~pentapod/miscpics/couple.jpg height=200 width=100.gif></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Love is for the Weak.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I'm in my 52nd level of power. The Neutralic powers I seek to fight are still way above me, and they shall continue to grow as the Planes of Power are revieled and our bodies are able to raise to new levels of power. Why am I so weakened, only now being able to crawl out of the Hole I was put in and stand above?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I'm in my 42nd level of power. The Neutralic powers I seek to fight are still above me, and they shall continue to grow as the Planes of Power are revealed and our bodies are able to rise to new levels of power. But why am I strengthened, why am I now soon able to crawl out of my youth and enter the Planes themselves?<br>
<br>
Because of Love!  Without light, there is no shadow.  Without heat, we do not know coldness.  Once I wandered, aimless, trying to serve Innoruuk.  Some tried to tell me of hatred, some lusted for me.  But then Innoruuk brought Tallonar to me, to conceive a child that would serve Him truly.  Do not tell me Love has weakened me.  In the light of Love, I have come to understand true Hate.  In defense of my child and husband, my Hate towards our enemies knows no bounds.  Loyalty to each other ... hatred and no mercy to our foes.<br>
<br>
Those broken souls you speak of did not know love ... they were seduced by lust, by the false promises of Erollisi Marr.  True Love is as unswerving and intense as true Hate, for it is the reverse side of the same coin.  Love is not pretty. It is not peace and harmony.  It is a burning flame that strengthens, a shield that protects the faithful, a sword that can be turned on the enemy.<br>
<br>
Your service to Hate is admirable.  But it's clear you do not yet understand its flip side, its shadow, its complement.<br>
