<br>
    Lady Didi - Without light, their is nothing but darkness. Those perceptive things are only used by Druids that try to convince us of an need for balance.<br>
<br>
The Balance between Heat and Cold.<br>
The Balance between Light and Dark.<br>
The Balance between Love and Hate.<br>
<br>
I tire of playing within Tunares worthless circle. I'll shatter these balances and take them off the deep end of Darkness. Without Love, their is only the Burning fuel of Hate.<br>
Love is a thing that lowers swords and brings forth acceptance. If Love had its way.. well look out there now. Woodelves and Darkelves Parade around with eachother in Happyness within places like Dreadstorm. Come now, I'm going to fight love because love is the source of all that is wrong with this world! Love has no bite, no fangs. It beguiles like an Enchanters spell, or the wave of some Various Females Hips or something of that nature. It lowers you down into half of what you are and then finishes you off with the final blow.<br>
<br>
But from this blow their can be a rise. Throught the Torment my hate has begun to toss away the final strings of sainity and in the way of Saryn, I'll rise to power and destroy what I seek to finish off.<br>
<br>
I personally believe that what you and Tallonar have is different from Love. A stronger bond where you KNOW that the each of you can rely on one another. This is all in theroy, I really have not figured out the details of this, but Its like an Ally, Undying trust in one another, or something like that. I refuse to call it love, for Love is for the Weak, and Neither you or High Knight Tallonar are weak. I'll figure it out, or try to.<br>
<br>
May the Father have .. No, The Father has no mercy for any lightbringer. <p><IMG SRC="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Shintou.gif" WIDTH="127" HEIGHT="110">
