<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> *tee hee!*</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
And don't go all foolish on yourself about what love is.  Love isn't the antithesis of hate -- that's apathy.  And love isn't what you need in order to hate -- that's passion, and not a small bit of a narrow mind.  Love isn't even getting angry and hurt when your lover loves someone else too -- that's envy, Lanys' playground.<br>
<br>
Love is when someone else's happiness is your happiness, when their joy is your joy, when caring for their well-being is a part of everything you have, everything you are, everything you ever hope to be.  As for whether it's strength or weakness...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> *shrug*</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
It's neither.  It simply Is.  Now what people DO about it can be strong or weak, depending on who they are and what choices they make.  But you can't blame or congratulate love, you just gotta blame or congratulate yourself.<br>
<br>
Just tell me... did you love Kallee?  Cause if not, oh BOY did you miss out!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
