<br>
&quot;Tell me, Shintou, how you feel about your god.  Do you hate him?  If so, for all of Norrath, why do you serve him?  If I have gathered true information, you kill for your god, you die for your god, you live for your god, you breathe, you walk, hunt, eat, survive, move, you EXIST for the Hate, for its spread, for its depth, for its purity.  These are similar qualities in the existance of love.&quot;  She shifts her weight to the other foot, angling her body in a gesture unconciously confident and self-knowing.  &quot;I would not, of course, say that you love your god either, for therein lies the almost-paradox of loving Hatred itself.<br>
<br>
&quot;If faced by Innoruuk, however, you would not turn your back to him.  You would not face him weaponless.  You would not trust him.  After all, the Darkness despises the weak, most especially of those who say they follow it.  Like a pack of wolves who hunt the rabbits and the drakes alike, the Darkness weeds out all frailty.  It would not be any different if you were to face Innoruuk.  To trust him - that key factor, TRUST - would be folly, and in it, a flawed death.<br>
<br>
&quot;I think that love is not the weakness that destroys those who cannot survive it.  Trusting those whom are untrustworthy, those who would knife you in the back as soon as your usefulness were through, is what is weak.<br>
<br>
&quot;Those who confuse love and trust can and do fall.  To see the beauty and love of another being can bring trust.  This trust can shape one's mind so that they believe that, like their lover, all is worthy of trust.  It is here where they fall, where they sink into a rose-tinted world of decadence.<br>
<br>
&quot;There are those who flit across Norrath, preaching that they 'love everybody and everything'.  This is not love, but a glut of trust.  Trust taken so far that it blinds, and it kills.  There are precious few who truly love all.  Precious few who would die to save a complete stranger's life.  How many Elves do you know of, followers of Erollsi Marr, who would die to save an alien Troll or Iksar?  I know of none, though I know of many who moralize to say they, like Erollsi, love all.&quot;<br>
<br>
She turns to address Solaneb.  &quot;While I agree with most of what you say, I must differ with you in your belief that those who abhor love 'simply need to find the right troll or ogre'.  To love one's god is enough.  To love existance, or to love oneself, or to love a figment such as money or power, that is enough.  To love aught else is to sully and dilute the single entity that is loved.<br>
<br>
&quot;To use myself as an example, I love and follow the Balance.  Bodiless and without tangible entity though it may be, I kill for the Balance, I die for the Balance, I live for the Balance, I breathe, I walk, hunt, eat, survive, move, I EXIST for the Balance and for my god.  I now walk the Dark path to serve my faith, and insodoing I follow those of the Darkness.  I aid them, I serve them, I am a companion to them, but I do not love them.  I once walked the path of the Light.  I aided those that follow the Light, I served them, was a companion to them, and trusted them because they could be trusted.  I did not love them.&quot;<br>
<br>
She hesitates a moment, and looks away.  &quot;I....  loved once, and it was a fool thing for me to do.  It lured me from my god and my faith.&quot;  She looks up again, determination a glowing radiation of green embers in her eyes.  &quot;I learned my lesson, of course.<br>
<br>
&quot;For me, there is nothing but the Balance and Karana.  For Shintou, there is nothing but the Hate and Innoruuk.&quot;<br>
<br>
That said, she pulls herself up onto one of the chairs and then onto a table built for too-talls, and perches there, a meditative look in her eyes.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eqsighost.netfirms.com/Amaeliya/forestsig.JPG "alt="The Keeper of the Balance//"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roninsenshi>RoninSenshi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia</span><br>  Posts: 1208<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/27/02 10:32:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Shintou3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Musings</span><hr size=1> Of course I hate Innoruuk. Why do I follow him however?<br>
Its simple. <br>
<br>
Hatred is true power. Its the only force that matters. I ally myself with those that can at least respect the trueness of those words. To Hate ones own Diety, can you understand what loathing that brings? What power? I hate even his Alter plane, there they have this Giant Version of Me running around, killing everyone. I really hate him, he's a pain. Right when we were able to fight there with relative ease, the Father brought down an entire new legion of stronger Minions, forcing us to ..replan.<br>
<br>
Anyhow. Innoruuk is power. That power is not easy to attain, if you go off and join the Lightbringers, you'll slowly lose that hate. You'll become like Cadien, like those in the Baston, like Demiath was. He became a Priest of Love, you know?<br>
<br>
They learned Tolerance from their lightbringer friends. Tolerance took from their hate. Soon enought, they loved, and no longer could handle hating the father. They became weak, and yes..<br>
<br>
Their is nothing worse to me.. then one of his own Children forsaking the Father.<br>
<br>
I was once there when I was young. I used to believe in the power of Malice.. or what was just an mistake on my part, for it just came out to be Weak Envy of Power. Thats where I learned to appricate death in its various forms.. But the Father came calling for me once again.<br>
<br>
I don't have the luxury to turn my back on him. I am his. I am special. Thats why he won't let me go, not even to another evil force. So the father came to me throught Rhael.<br>
<br>
And he taught me to hate everything he is.<br>
<br>
Trust? Putting so much faith in another is foolish. Its how you get used. Hate is all, and its what I use to find out truth.<br>
<br>
Lightbringer or Child of Darkness, I'll treat you like a lightbringer until you produce what proof you have that you are Dark. Most of the time this gets me makes me look foolish, but its worth it to find out who is friend or foe.<br>
<br>
So thats why I hate Innoruuk, and continue to follow his path. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Shintou.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kimayasilverbark>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://prod.bsis.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/15/15568/folders/6507/67125button-wolf-pawprint" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tao Te Bark</span><br>  Posts: 502<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/29/02 11:40:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Musings</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kimaya slowly blinks her eyes back into focus, having drifted off into a reverie about someone special.  Shintou's words catch up to her, and she just starts giggling again.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Oh, Sillyshins, powermongering is for the weak!  Seeking power over others is a poor balm for lacking power over oneself.  No matter how you run around yelling and screaming, how many blades you bloody or hearts you break, it won't bring you knowing.  It won't bring you understanding.  It won't bring you the power you lack.<br>
<br>
Your race are who they are because they were stolen away, and were not strong enough to hold out against Captain Hateyhead's torments and suffering forever, were not strong enough to keep their sense of Self.  You are who you are because you were stolen away, and were not strong enough to hold out against your own personal hateyhead's torments and suffering, were not strong enough to keep your sense of Self.  So you lash out blindly, spinning madly, furiously storming your dance of blindness as you try to blind all others so you don't have to open your eyes, trying desperately to justify all you've suffered rather than face that it may have all just been bad mistakes and sad misdeeds.  For all you've suffered, that pain would hurt too much.<br>
<br>
So go on, be a slave to hate struggling to expand his master's grasp, cry out to the world how your beloved bonds make you strong.  See how strong your hate is when it bangs against the bastion of grounded Self Knowing.  See how effective your storms are when they wail against the bastion of Inner Peace.  See how well you can wound with your sticks and stones when someone simply refuses to stand within your tiny circle.<br>
<br>
You know I'd love to help you see so many things, but only you can open your eyes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Shrugging, she turns back to a clump of feathers she's been sewing onto a piece of cloth, happily singing to herself.<br>
<br>
Rant on, rant on, Shintou Shinai<br>
Rant on, rant on; 'tis all in vain!<br>
You throw the sand against the wind,<br>
And the wind blows it back again.<br>
