<br>
I am that apathy.<br>
<br>
Your craving emotional needs are laid bare before the cleansing touch of Pain. The bright ardor of your passions are like a blazing candle which must eventually burn itself out. The path of Torment is a frozen flame, unchanging and eternal. Only when all desires have been renounced can the clarity of the Dark Truth be revealed.<br>
<br>
The inherent imperfections of this world...of Life, will be cleansed in the Void and remade in the process of Instrumentality. The Project continues. Third Impact is coming. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.angelfire.com/anime4/fyanna/snk_kojirou3.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Fyanna</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Fell Knight of Thule<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Hitokiri to the League of Shadows<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> There can be no salvation without destruction,</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> no hope this side of death..</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=severothfv>SeverothFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/30/02 6:06:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Musings</span><hr size=1>  Love? We could argue FOREVER, and never find a &quot;true&quot; answer. Is love when you are willing to die for another...or is that weakness, lack of self preservation? Is love &quot;letting go&quot; of the one you love? Hoping beyond hope that your love returns to you? Or is that lack of self esteem or pride and letting someone &quot;play&quot; with you and walk away? *grins* Who knows? Maybe in death we will find out *grins and says in a dark whisper*...maybe not.<br>
